y><administrativeArea>Taiwan</administrativeArea><postalCode>10066</postalCode><country>R.O.C.</country></address><phone phonetype="voice">886-2-23039978 ext. 1613</phone><phone phonetype="fax">886-2-23752164</phone><electronicMailAddress>wangch@tfri.gov.tw</electronicMailAddress><role>Water quality</role></associatedParty><abstract><para>Ecological monitoring sites of riparian zones was established along Chungliao and Shanping creeks within Liukuei Experimental Forest for measurement of streamflow characteristics, water quality variation, streambed stability, vegetation diversity, wildlife species, and freshwater fishes density. If streamflow characteristics, water quality variation, streambed stability, vegetaion diversity, wildlife species, and freshwater fishes  density still kept good condition during the past monitoring periods, the riparian management of Liukuei Experimental Forest do not need a special conservation planning. If streamflow characteristics, water quality variation, streambed stability, vegetation diversity, wildlife species, and freshwater density were getting to worse condition, a special  improvement conservation planning would be necessary in the riparian management of Liukuei Experimental Forest.</para></abstract><keywordSet><keyword>Riparian zones</keyword><keyword>Stormflow</keyword><keyword>Water quality</keyword><keyword>Vegetation</keyword></keywordSet><intellectualRights><para>Please contact with data set owner</para></intellectualRights><coverage scope="document"><temporalCoverage scope="document"><rangeOfDates><beginDate><calendarDate>2004-01-01</calendarDate></beginDate><endDate><calendarDate>2008-12-31</calendarDate></endDate></rangeOfDates></temporalCoverage><geographicCoverage scope="document"><geographicDescription>Chungliao and Shanping Creeks, Liukuei, Kaoshung County, Taiwan</geographicDescription><boundingCoordinates><westBoundingCoordinate>120.6583</westBoundingCoordinate><eastBoundingCoordinate>120.7167</eastBoundingCoor